description.narrative:
The project is specifically targeting HIV positive and/or affected women in Blantyre Rural District where DAPP recently implemented a 3-year HIV and AIDS programme known as Total Control of the Epidemic (TCE). The areas face chronic poverty and acute food challenges among others, as noted by DAPP during the implementation of TCE project. The situation is attributed to inadequate access to agricultural resources and technologies by women who are engaged in agriculture. The impacts of HIV/AIDS further exacerbate the poor economic status  of the households. Although HIV/AIDS has a significant impact upon all households, the effects of the epidemic are more on impoverished families and women.

This project’s direct impact will be on 6,000 women farmers and their household members estimated to be about 33,000 in total (average household size is about 5.5 members). (the 6000 female farmers would be those  who were already identified as being HIV positive and participated in a previous DAPP TCE  Project) 

The indirect beneficiaries of this project are estimated to be above 99,000 farmers (approx. 50,000 female  and 49,000 male farmers). ;
